news.title: Piramal Capital Housing Finance's former MD, two others pay Rs 44 crore to settle Sebi probe
news.para: According to Sebi's order, the three entities accrued illegal gains worth nearly Rs 16 crore after buying shares of Piramal Enterprises (holding company) using unpublished price sensitive information.

news.title: Chandigarh revokes building plans, OC of Godrej Properties' commercial project
news.para: "We strongly believe that the order was passed based on a wrong premise and a misunderstanding of the facts. We are reviewing the order's contents and will contest this decision in the appropriate forum in accordance with the law," the company said.

news.title: DLF's sales bookings jump over three-fold to Rs 6,404 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: DLF has given guidance to achieve Rs 17,000 crore worth of sales bookings for the entire 2024-25 financial year as against nearly Rs 15,000 crore in the preceding year.

news.title: Godrej Properties raises Rs 1,275 crore through issues of non-convertible debentures
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing on Friday, the company said the allotment committee of the board of directors of the company approved the allotment of 93,540 unsecured redeemable NCDs of the face value of Rs 1 lakh each, aggregating to Rs 935.40 crore.

news.title: Godrej Industries Group's family office pares 4.4% stake in Sobha for Rs 858 crore
news.para: According to the exchange data, Anamudi Real Estates LLP offloaded 47.37 lakh shares, amounting to a 4.43 per cent stake in Sobha Ltd.

news.title: Metro Bank to sell residential mortgages portfolio to NatWest for $3 billion
news.para: NatWest also bought the banking business of UK retailer Sainsbury's in June, while Nationwide Building Society is buying Virgin Money and Coventry Building Society is taking over The Co-operative Bank.

news.title: Flagstar Bank to sell residential mortgage servicing business for $1.4 billion
news.para: New York Community Bancorp has struggled in the past year with its acquisition of Signature Bank, one of a pair of banks that failed in early 2023 due to rising interest rates.

news.title: Holcim cuts full-year sales outlook after U.S. downturn
news.para: In the first results under new CEO Miljan Gutovic, Holcim reduced its outlook for sales growth to the low single-digit percentage range from its previous outlook for growth above 6%.

news.title: Raipur civic body asks builders to construct 50 rainwater harvesting pits each
news.para: The RMC has set a target of constructing 50,000 rainwater harvesting pits including 20,000 pits in the current monsoon season. A single pit can conserve 2 lakh litres of rainwater.

news.title: Rent dues mount, stores at Gurugram's rapid rail station sealed
news.para: A total of 1,956 sq ft, covering seven shops, is registered under owner, Sunil Miglani, said sub-divisional engineer Naresh Kumar Rana.

news.title: Over 23,800 people in Delhi received ownership rights of properties under PM-UDAY: Govt
news.para: ​In a written reply to a question, Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Tokhan Sahu said the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has received 1,22,729 applications for ownership rights under the PM-UDAY.

news.title: WeWork India adds over 1.4 lakh sq ft with new centers in Bengaluru and Noida
news.para: WeWork 37 Cunningham is a four-story workspace with over 1,000 desks across over 60,000 sq ft while WeWork Galaxy Business Park has over 1,400 desks across 79,000 sq ft.

news.title: Synq.work plans to invest Rs 60 crore to add six lakh sq ft in Bengaluru, Pune & Hyderabad
news.para: Synq.Work plans to expand the current seating capacity from 3,200 to 12,000 by adding an additional 8800 seats by December 2025

news.title: Home First Finance Company's net profit up 27% at Rs 88 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Its assets under management grew 35% on year to Rs. 10,478 crores, while loan disbursement grew 30% on year to Rs. 1,163 crores. About 86% of its portfolio comprises housing loans with average ticket size of Rs 11.6 lakh.

news.title: NCLT approves Alchemist Infra Realty's acquisition by Vantage Point Asset Management
news.para: The company’s resolution professional had received a claim of Rs 1,293 crore and the successful bidder is paying about Rs 470 crore to acquire the company through the insolvency resolution process.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' net profit down 51% to Rs 36.57 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: ​The company posted a net profit of Rs 74.36 crore during the April-June quarter of the previous fiscal, The Ramco Cements said in a regulatory filing.
